er bilby Macrotis lagotis using the metapopulation model Analysis of the Likelihood of Extinction (Alex) (1995) Biological Conservation, 73, pp. 151-160; Stockwell, D.R.B., Peters, D.P., The GARP modelling system: Problems and solutions to automated spatial prediction (1999) International Journal of Geographic Information Systems, 13, pp. 143-158; Stockwell, D.R.B., Peterson, A.T., Controlling bias in biodiversity data (2002) Predicting Species Occurrences: Issues of Scale and Accuracy, pp. 537-546. , eds J.M. Scott, P.J. Heglund & M.L. Morrison, pp, Island Press, Washington, DC, USA; Stockwell, D.R.B., Peterson, A.T., Effects of sample size on accuracy of species distribution models (2002) Ecological Modelling, 148, pp. 1-13; Stoms, D.M., Davis, F.W., Cogan, C.B., Painho, M.O., Duncan, B.W., Scepan, J., Scott, J.M., Geographic analysis of California Condor sighting data (1993) Conservation Biology, 7, pp. 148-159; Thomas, C.D., Cameron, A., Green, R.E., Bakkenes, M., Beaumont, L.J., Collingham, Y.C., Erasmus, B.F.N., Williams, S.E., Extinction risk from climate change (2004) Nature, 427, pp. 145-148; (1997) Hydro 1k Elevation Derivative Database, , http:// edc.usgs.gov/products/ elevation/gtopo30/hydro/index. html, USGS United States Geological Survey, Sioux Falls, USA, accessed 20 February; Wolf, C.M., Garland Jr, T., Griffith, B., Predictors of avian and mammalian translocation success: Reanalysis with phylogenetically independent contrasts (1998) Biological Conservation, 86, pp. 243-255","Peterson, A.T.; Natural History Museum, University of Kansas, Lawrence, KS 66045, United States; email: town@ku.edu",,,,,,,,00306053,,ORYXA,,"English","ORYX",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-33846056901
